label: University of Pennsylvania Ms. Codex 762: Alphabetum malarum mulierum ... etc.
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Three works, apparently unrelated: a misogynist alphabet consisting largely of quotations from classical authors and from the Bible, a collection of excerpts from Aristotle with extensive marginal commentary, and Petrarch's Psalmi poenitentiales.
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 28-33 long lines; ruled in lead.
        Script: Written in a Gothic cursive script by several different hands.
        Decoration: 
        Binding: Modern paper-covered boards.
        Origin: Written in Italy in the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn Ms. Codex 762
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 2487510 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/2487510
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/PennManuscripts/html/mscodex762.html
